---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";
---

<MainLayout
  title="About"
  pathname={Astro.url.pathname}
  description="Authoritative background on the GUARDIANS program, funding context, coordination model, and current draft scope."
>
  <section class="page-header stack-md">
    <span class="eyebrow">Program background</span>
    <h1>About GUARDIANS</h1>
    <p>
      GUARDIANS is a national infrastructure program focused on secure discovery, access, stewardship, and analysis pathways for sensitive human omics data in Australia.
    </p>
    <p class="draft-note">
      Funding wording and current-state details here are draft interpretations of the supplied background material and should be replaced with approved program copy when available.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-card stack-md">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Overview</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Program overview</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      The program exists because Australian human omics research depends on nationally coordinated infrastructure that can support discovery, controlled access, and scalable analysis without weakening stewardship or governance obligations.
    </p>
    <p>
      The supplied materials consistently position GUARDIANS as infrastructure for researchers, data custodians, and delivery partners working with sensitive datasets that cross institutional boundaries.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-card">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Timeline</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Program timeline</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline__item">
        <strong>Total program length</strong>
        <p>3.5 years across two phases, with Phase I covering two years and Phase II covering 18 months.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline__item">
        <strong>Current state</strong>
        <p>The IA states the program is 18 months into Phase I. The background one-pager separately says implementation activities are underway and deployment continues through 2027.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline__item">
        <strong>Roadmap baseline</strong>
        <p>The supplied roadmap uses Q1 2026 as its strategic baseline for national capability planning.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-card stack-md">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Coordination</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Coordination and delivery</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      Australian BioCommons coordinates the program, with delivery distributed across national partners contributing identity and access capability, infrastructure operations, repository and commons capability, stewardship, governance expertise, and research translation.
    </p>
    <p>
      The background materials also frame GUARDIANS as part of the broader national digital research infrastructure ecosystem, aligning with international standards and Australian ethical, legal, and social requirements.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-card stack-md">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Funding</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Funding acknowledgement</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      Draft acknowledgement: the supplied materials state that GUARDIANS is funded by NCRIS through Bioplatforms Australia and coordinated by Australian BioCommons.
    </p>
    <p>
      Approved acknowledgement text was not included in the workspace, so this wording should be replaced before publication.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-card stack-md">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Scope</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Program scope and guidelines</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      The current prototype catalogue covers services and resources that can be supported directly by the supplied materials, including infrastructure components, guidance, roadmap outputs, and public communication artefacts.
    </p>
    <p>
      Program guidelines emphasise national focus, sustainability, interoperability, governance, security, training, and service operations. See the <a href="/services-resources#guardians-guidelines">guidelines entry</a> and the <a href="/services-resources#human-omics-capability-roadmap">roadmap entry</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-card stack-md">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Related links</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Related program paths</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Services &amp; resources</h3>
        <p>The catalogue is the most concrete view of program delivery in this prototype.</p>
        <a class="card__link" href="/services-resources">Open the catalogue</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Partners &amp; contributions</h3>
        <p>Browse structured attribution and see how partner work maps to catalogue items.</p>
        <a class="card__link" href="/partners-contributions">View partner entries</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Contact</h3>
        <p>Use the shared contact pathway for enquiries about collaboration, media, or access questions.</p>
        <a class="card__link" href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>Email the team</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
